Nigerians have opted for the use of Virtual Private Networks (VPNs) to circumvent the suspension of Twitter by the Federal Government. On Friday, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, Minister of Information, announced the suspension of the social media platform’s operation in Nigeria. The minister based the action on the persistent use of the platform for activities that are capable of undermining Nigeria’s corporate existence. Many have expressed dissatisfaction with the development, highlighting the benefits of the microblogging site. Below are some reactions.        